<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1395,1997]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1466,1492]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[284,374,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
A–E). Wingspan, 
<quantity box="[578,660,1467,1493]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
. Head orange yellow, with slender, erect scales on vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1424,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
). Antenna black, with whitish apex; its proximal third orange yellow ventrally. Labial palpus extremely large, sickleshaped; first two segments orange yellow, third segment partially black. Thorax orange yellow. Abdomen black dorsally. Legs orange yellow, with blackish/greyish zones on tarsi, notably on fore- and midlegs. Tibial spurs 0-2-4; the medial pair of hindleg from middle of tibia (
<figureCitation box="[697,803,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of forewing: black, with orange yellow base; fringe yellow with two black regions: a small one at the apex, a large one at the tornus. Forewing ventral surface: like dorsal surface but with reduced, ill-defined basal yellow spot. Hind wing dark grey on both surfaces; fringe greyish (becoming whitish distally). Forewing venation (
<figureCitation box="[859,962,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
): all veins free, separate, except for 
<collectionCode box="[1362,1381,1719,1745]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1381,1389,1737,1751]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">4</subScript>
and 
<collectionCode box="[151,170,1755,1781]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[170,178,1773,1787]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">5</subScript>
which are stalked (the latter running to termen, just below apex); 
<collectionCode box="[919,938,1755,1781]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[937,945,1773,1787]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2</subScript>
arising approximately midway between 
<collectionCode box="[1404,1427,1755,1781]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
1 and 
<collectionCode box="[200,219,1791,1817]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[218,226,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
(slightly nearer 
<collectionCode box="[411,430,1791,1817]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[430,438,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
); bases of 
<collectionCode box="[564,583,1791,1817]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[582,590,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[672,680,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
both moderately remote from 
<collectionCode box="[1029,1048,1791,1817]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1048,1074,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">4+5</subScript>
; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1114,1122,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2</subScript>
arising closer to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1345,1353,1809,1823]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[176,184,1845,1859]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
; CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[252,260,1845,1859]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[368,376,1845,1859]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2</subScript>
arched, close to each other proximally; CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[880,888,1845,1859]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
arising near M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1059,1067,1845,1859]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
. Hind wing venation (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1424,1827,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
): Rs and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[263,271,1881,1895]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
long-stalked; upper edge of discal cell very short, slightly shorter than stem Rs+M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1216,1224,1881,1895]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
; discocellular m1- m2 long, strongly oblique; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[483,491,1917,1931]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[600,608,1917,1931]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
short-stalked; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[802,810,1917,1931]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2</subScript>
arising near M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[982,990,1917,1931]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">3</subScript>
+CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1059,1067,1917,1931]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
. Abdominal segments (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1428,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 19J</figureCitation>
) without spinose zones; sternum II without anterolateral processes but with short apodemes, distinct venulae, and an arched, transverse ridge near its anterior edge.
</paragraph>
