</emphasis>
: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,876]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[199,391,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[407,499,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
F–I): See also the line drawing given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P. E. L." box="[963,1106,151,177]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref24658" refString="Viette, P. E. L. (1986) Nouveaux Microlepidopteres de Madagascar (Oecophoridae et Gelechiidae) (New species of Malagasy Microlepidoptera-Oecophoridae and Gelechiidae). Bulletin mensuel de la Societe linneenne de Lyon, 55 (4), 109 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1986.10753" type="journal article" year="1986">Viette (1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1202,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,780,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-179@19.[151,1437,771,1895]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Torodora hildebrandtella (Viette, [1957]), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, male genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 2757; C'; close-up of uncus, gen. prep. no. CIS-7385/Park; D, aedeagus; E, abdomen; F, forewing venation, specimen from Zahamena. Scale bar for the genitalia and aedeagus: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406488/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Ductus bursae narrow, very long, about 3 times the length of the corpus bursae, with an elongate, colliculate, heavily sclerotized plate in posterior 2/5; ductus seminalis narrow, arising approximately from middle of ductus bursae. Corpus bursae rounded, with a pair of large scobinate signa. Ovipositor elongate; apophyses posteriores thinner and much longer than apophyses anteriores (length ratio of ca. 3 to 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,745,334,362]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,876]" box="[199,745,334,362]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,334,360]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,494,335,361]" name="Madagascar" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(West) (
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P. E. L." box="[590,733,335,362]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref24658" refString="Viette, P. E. L. (1986) Nouveaux Microlepidopteres de Madagascar (Oecophoridae et Gelechiidae) (New species of Malagasy Microlepidoptera-Oecophoridae and Gelechiidae). Bulletin mensuel de la Societe linneenne de Lyon, 55 (4), 109 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1986.10753" type="journal article" year="1986">Viette, 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,876]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,372,398]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[324,470,371,397]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
“ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" box="[334,460,371,397]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Idiopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Idiopteryx</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Viette, 1986" authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1986" box="[479,735,371,397]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Odites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obitsyella">
<emphasis box="[479,588,371,397]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">obitsyella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P. E. L." box="[596,735,371,397]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref24658" refString="Viette, P. E. L. (1986) Nouveaux Microlepidopteres de Madagascar (Oecophoridae et Gelechiidae) (New species of Malagasy Microlepidoptera-Oecophoridae and Gelechiidae). Bulletin mensuel de la Societe linneenne de Lyon, 55 (4), 109 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1986.10753" type="journal article" year="1986">Viette, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lvovsky" authorityYear="1996" box="[1032,1128,371,397]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oditinae">Oditinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1145,1300,371,398]" class="Insecta" family="Peleopodidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Peleopodidae</taxonomicName>
) and, tentatively, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1891" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" box="[256,547,408,434]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Odites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[256,329,408,434]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Odites</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walsingham" box="[335,547,408,434]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="63 - 132" refId="ref24901" refString="Walsingham, [T. de G.] (1891) African Micro-Lepidoptera. Transactions of the entomological Society of London, 1891 (1), 63 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1891. tb 01643. x" type="journal article" year="1891">Walsingham, 1891</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a speciose genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[781,916,408,434]" name="Madagascar" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(and elsewhere). It differs from most 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lecithoceridae</taxonomicName>
in its vertex vestiture, mainly composed of slender erect scales (while vertex tends to be smooth-scaled in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,322,482,509]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lecithoceridae</taxonomicName>
), and in its metathoracic coxae, which lack the rows of erect piliform scales that are normally present, postero-ventrally, in the 
<taxonomicName box="[478,648,519,545]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lecithoceridae</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1986" box="[784,974,519,545]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Odites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obitsyella">
<emphasis box="[784,974,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Odites obitsyella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows, on the dorsal surface of the hind wing, a few piliform scales that arise from the lower edge of the discal cell; as mentioned above (see remarks about 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,294,593,618]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Mexytocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,294,593,618]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Mexytocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), we regard this “cubital pecten” as a previously unnoticed autapomorphy of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lvovsky" authorityYear="1996" box="[1217,1313,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oditinae">Oditinae</taxonomicName>
(nevertheless also present, through parallel evolution, in at least core 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" box="[822,968,629,655]" class="Insecta" family="Xyloryctidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Xyloryctidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stainton" authorityYear="1854" box="[1023,1161,629,655]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gelechiidae</taxonomicName>
: Dichomerinae). Typical oditine characters found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1986" box="[455,598,666,692]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Odites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obitsyella">
<emphasis box="[455,598,666,692]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">O. obitsyella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also include: very large, slender, sickle-shaped labial palpi; hind wing with long-stalked Rs and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[408,416,721,735]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
, a very short upper edge of discal cell, and a long, markedly oblique discocellular m1-m2 (compare with the figures given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lvovsky, A. L." box="[567,762,739,766]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="650 - 659" refId="ref23494" refString="Lvovsky, A. L. (1996) Composition of the genus Odites Wlsm. and its position in the classification of the Gelechioidea (Lepi- doptera). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 75 (3), 650 - 659. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1996">Lvovsky (1996))</bibRefCitation>
; elongate ovipositor (with long apophyses posteriores); on abdominal sternum II, presence of a well indicated, narrow transverse ridge, which lies near the anterior edge of the sternum (
<figureCitation box="[257,353,813,839]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-25@26.[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Odites obitsyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, ventral surface of fore- and hind wings; C, lateral view of head; D, hindleg in lateral view; E, labels; F, female genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 5706; G, ditto, ovipositor; H, ditto, posterior section of ductus bursae; I, ditto, corpus bursae; J, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406498/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 19J</figureCitation>
). Occurrence of the last trait (also present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1989" box="[861,1004,814,839]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Mexytocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,1004,814,839]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Mexytocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) requires however further checking in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lvovsky" authorityYear="1996" box="[311,411,850,876]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oditinae">Oditinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
